title: (x) Undisguised / ultra-condensed stressed sans - probably custom - similar to Obelysk, Empire, Giorgio Sans, Keyboard {gang}
author: scottsullivan

comments.content: Empire is close, but not the one.

Hi Scott,  
this one came up [before](http://web.archive.org/web/20131015063735/http:/www.typophile.com/node/46831) and [before](http://web.archive.org/web/20131015063735/http:/www.typophile.com/node/63598).  
F
thanks Florian! I'm guessing this is a custom one then cause it doesn't seem to be completely solved-

The contrast on this N, for example, is backwards from all the contrasted sans I have been finding. However, it's just like the narrow serif fonts, like [Keyboard](http://web.archive.org/web/20131015063735/http:/new.myfonts.com/fonts/redrooster/keyboard-rr/). It's not exact (the G chin is too high, and the S spine is not the same), but it would be a better approximation of what appears to be a custom font, if you removed the serifs from such a font.

- Mike Yanega
